The issue with your code is that you're assigning `item.cost` to the variab
variable `total` in every iteration of the loop, so by the time you get to 
the end of the array, `total` will be just the last item's cost and not the
their total sum. 

We need to accumulate the total costs instead of replacing it with each new
new value from `item.cost`:

```tundra
val items = [
  { name: "a", cost: 2 },
  { name: "b", cost: 3 },
  { name: "c", cost: 4 }
];

var total = 0;
for (item in items) {
  total += item.cost;
}

print(total);
```
